    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PHONE MERGER TALKS END</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Merger talks between Royal KPN of Netherlands and Telefonica of Spain break down in face of opposition from minority group within Telefonica board (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Talks about a merger between two leading European telecommunication companies -- Royal KPN of the Netherlands and Telefonica of Spain -- broke down. It would have been the first merger of two state-owned phone monopolies. The companies said that a majority of the Telefonica board backed the deal but that opposition ''by an important minority group within the board'' undermined KPN's confidence in the chance for success of the new company.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
